Tabraiz Shamsi, the left-arm wrist-spinner, has left South Africa's tour of Sri Lanka for family reasons. No date has been set for his return.Shamsi took four wickets in his first red-ball Test in Galle last week, which South Africa lost by 278 runs.Should Shamsi not return in time, uncapped legspinner Shaun von Berg could make his Test debut at the Sinhalese Sports Club in Colombo.